@page "/privacy"
@inject IAuthService AuthService

<PageTitle>Privacy</PageTitle>

<LegalDocument Eyebrow="Your information"
               Title="Privacy at MiniPainterHub"
               Summary="This pilot privacy notice explains what MiniPainterHub collects, why it is used, and the choices available to community members.">
    <section>
        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <p>Account information includes your username, email address, password credential managed by ASP.NET Core Identity, account roles, sign-in methods, and account restriction history. Google and Discord sign-in store the selected provider’s stable account identifier and verified email association, but not provider access or refresh tokens.</p>
        <p>Profile and community information includes display name, biography, avatar, posts, images, painting guides, comments, likes, follows, direct messages, reports, and support conversations you choose to create.</p>
        <p>Hobby Project information includes project metadata, status and dates, milestone labels, showcase order, cover choices, and the relationships between a project and your existing posts. Archiving or editing a project does not delete those posts.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>How information is used</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Authenticate accounts and protect access to personal or administrative features.</li>
            <li>Publish and organize the hobby content and social interactions you request.</li>
            <li>Operate support, safety, moderation, abuse prevention, and service reliability workflows.</li>
            <li>Diagnose technical failures and measure application performance using limited operational logs.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Service providers and disclosure</h2>
        <p>MiniPainterHub uses Microsoft Azure to host application, database, image-storage, and account-email infrastructure. If you choose Google or Discord sign-in, that provider processes the authentication interaction under its own privacy terms. Information may also be disclosed when required for security, legal compliance, or protection of community members. MiniPainterHub does not sell personal information.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Retention and security</h2>
        <p>Account and community records are retained while needed to operate the service, preserve conversations and moderation history, meet security obligations, or resolve support issues. Short-lived external-authentication exchanges expire after ten minutes and are cleaned from active use. Transport encryption, access controls, password hashing, and restricted administrative roles protect stored information, but no online service can promise absolute security.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Your choices</h2>
        <p>You can edit your public profile, choose whether to connect Google or Discord, set a local password, and disconnect an external provider once another sign-in method exists. Signed-in users can contact administrators through the <a href="/support">Support Center</a> to ask questions or request account-data review or deletion. Some safety, audit, or legal records may need to be retained.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        @if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(_supportEmail))
        {
            <p data-testid="privacy-support-email">Privacy and account requests can be sent to <a href="mailto:@_supportEmail">@_supportEmail</a>.</p>
        }
        else
        {
            <p>Signed-in community members can contact the administrators through the <a href="/support">Support Center</a>. A public support email will be displayed here before external sign-in is activated.</p>
        }
    </section>
</LegalDocument>

@code {
    private string? _supportEmail;

    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        _supportEmail = (await AuthService.GetProvidersAsync()).SupportEmail;
    }
}
